The '''Spanish Newspaper Publishers' Association''' ({{lang-es|Asociación de Editores de Diarios Españoles}}; '''AEDE''') is a [[trade association]] for Spanish [[newspaper publisher]]s based in [[Madrid]], [[Spain]].
The AEDE has campaigned against [[news aggregator]]s' use of newspaper website content without payment to publishers, and successfully lobbied for Spanish [[copyright]] law to be amended<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boe.es/boe/dias/2014/11/05/pdfs/BOE-A-2014-11404.pdf|title=Ley 21/2014, de 4 de noviembre, por la que se modifica el texto refundido de la Ley de Propiedad Intelectual, aprobado por Real Decreto Legislativo 1/1996, de 12 de abril, y la Ley 1/2000, de 7 de enero, de Enjuiciamiento Civil|publisher=Agencia Estatal Boletín Oficial del Estado|date=November 2014}}</ref> in 2014 to require Spanish publishers to charge news aggregators for using Spanish news material, regardless of whether individual publishers might wish to waive those charges.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/business/currency/spain-versus-internet|title=Spain Versus the Internet|publisher=The New Yorker|date= 13 December 2014|author= Vauhini Vara}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://blogs.wsj.com/digits/2014/12/15/spains-publishers-brace-for-pain-over-google-news-shutdown/|title=Spain’s Publishers Brace for Google News Shutdown | publisher=Wall Street Journal | date = 15 December 2014 | author=David Roman}}</ref> In response, [[Google]] announced that they would be shutting down the Spanish version of their [[Google News]] service.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2014/dec/11/google-news-spain-to-close-in-response-to-tax-on-story-links|title=Google News Spain to close in response to story links 'tax' |publisher=[[The Guardian]]|date= 11 December 2014|author=Dominic Rushe}}</ref>
The AEDE reacted by lobbying the Spanish government to force Google to keep it running.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.techdirt.com/articles/20141212/07360229413/surprise-spanish-newspapers-beg-government-eu-to-stop-google-news-shutting-down.shtml|title=Surprise: Spanish Newspapers Beg Government And EU To Stop Google News Shutting Down|publisher=Techdirt|date=12 Dec 2014|author=Glyn Moody}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theregister.co.uk/2014/12/14/spain_google_news_aede_volte_face/|title=Hold the front page: Spain's anti-Google lobbyists lobby for Google News return|publisher=The Register|date=14 Dec 2014 |author=Kelly Fiveash}}</ref>
Google shut down its Spanish edition of Google News on 16 December 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thespainreport.com/13331/google-news-spain-taken-offline-google-fulfills-promise-response-aede-copyright-law/ |title=Google News In Spain Taken Offline After Google Fulfills Promise In Response To AEDE Copyright Law |publisher=The Spain Report |author=Matthew Bennett |date=16 December 2014 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141224165335/https://www.thespainreport.com/13331/google-news-spain-taken-offline-google-fulfills-promise-response-aede-copyright-law/ |archivedate=24 December 2014 }}</ref> It also announced that it had removed Spanish publishers from Google News.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://support.google.com/news/answer/6140047#English|title=Google Noticias en España|publisher=[[Google]]|accessdate=2014-12-24}}</ref>
