[[File:Frans Hals - Pieter Jacobsz Olycan - sn251.jpg|thumb|right|Pieter Jacobsz Olycan, by Frans Hals]] '''Pieter Jacobsz Olycan''' (1572 &ndash; 1658), was a Dutch brewer, magistrate, and later mayor of [[Haarlem]], best known today for his portraits by [[Frans Hals]], as well as for the portraits of his wife [[Maritge Claesdr. Voogt]].
==Biography== [[File:Frans Hals - portrait of Pieter Jacobsz Olycan at bust length OS-2004-39.JPG|thumb|Previously assumed to be a copy of the 3/4 length portrait, this smaller panel by Frans Hals is now considered to predate it by 5 years or so.]] He was a merchant in oils and grains in Amsterdam with a warehouse called "In den Olycan", which became his name. He was also a brewer in Haarlem on the [[Spaarne]] river with a large brewery called the "Vogelstruys".<ref>This was situated on the Donkere Spaarne next to the brewery "De Vos"</ref> Pieter Olycan was one of three brewers from Haarlem who sold his “Vogelstruys” beer from a 'bierstekerij' on the Bierkade in [[Purmerend]].<ref>[http://www.oneindignoordholland.nl/nl-NL/verhaal/810/biertje Story of beer in Purmerend] on [[Oneindig Noord Holland]]</ref> He married Maritje Claesdr Voogt and through her he became the brother-in-law to two more brewers of Haarlem. They became the parents of:<ref>Frans Hals: Exhibition on the Occasion of the Centenary of the Municipal Museum at Haarlem, 1862-1962., pp 58-59, publication Frans Hals Museum, 1962</ref><ref name=Biesboer>[https://books.google.com/books?id=1mV6p35NufEC&pg=PA8 Collections of paintings in Haarlem, 1572-1745], by P Biesboer; Carol Togneri, Los Angeles, Getty Provenance Index, Getty Research Institute, 2001</ref> # [[Jacob Pietersz Olycan|Jacob]], who later followed in his father's footsteps # Dorothea, who married Cornelis van Loo of brewery ''De Drie Leliën'' # IJsbrant, who studied law # Volckje, who married [[Johan Schatter]] # [[Nicolaes Olycan|Nicolaes]], who married Agatha Dicx of brewery [[Het Scheepje, Haarlem|Het Scheepje]] # [[Maria Pietersdr Olycan|Maria]], who married the brewer [[Andries van Hoorn]] # Hester, who married [[Tyman Oosdorp]]
Pieter Olycan was a member of the Haarlem regency and became a magistrate and mayor of Haarlem, and served in the Haarlem Cluveniers Civic guard. He was portrayed by [[Hendrik Gerritsz Pot]] in his [[The Officers of the St Adrian Militia Company in 1630|group portrait of the St Adrian Civic Guard in 1630]]. <gallery> File:Hendrik Gerritsz Pot 1630 cluveniersdoelen haarlem.jpg|Olycan is second from left in Pot's schutterstuk File:Portrait of Maritge Claesdr. Voogt (1577-1644) by Frans Hals 027.jpg|His wife Maritge Claesdr Voogt File:Frans Hals - Cornelia Claesdr Vooght - WGA11112.jpg|Her sister, Cornelia Claesdr Vooght File:Frans Hals - Willem Claesz Vooght as Colonel in 1627 schutterstuk.jpg|Her brother [[Willem Claesz Vooght]] as colonel in Hals' 1627 schutterstuk File:Haarlem - Donkere Spaarne 50.JPG|Former brewery ''Vogelstruys'' on the Spaarne in Haarlem File:WLM - M.arjon - Purmerend Bierkade 9 (1).jpg|Bierkade 9 in Purmerend, still called “De Vogelstruys” </gallery> <gallery> File:Frans Hals - Portrait of Jacob Olycan - Mauritshuis 459.jpg|Their son [[Jacob Pietersz Olycan|Jacob]] File:Frans Hals - Maria Pietersdochter Olycan-1.jpg|Their daughter Maria </gallery>
